Jim Ned Parents & Fans:

The JV football game scheduled for Thursday 9/10/20 @ Eastland has been moved to Jim Ned due to field conditions in Eastland. In order to accommodate this change, the 7th and 8th grade start times have changed as well. Football games scheduled Thursday (9/10) will be played at the following times:

7th grade - 4:00 pm
8th grade - 5:30 pm or approximately 10 mins after the conclusion of the previous game.
Junior Varsity - 7:00 pm or approximately 10 mins after the conclusion of the previous game.

All tickets purchased for the JV game in Eastland will be refunded. Fans may purchase tickets for the Junior High & Junior Varsity games at Jim Ned Stadium on our website at the Tickets tab.

The JV Football Game scheduled for tonight (8/27/20) vs Ballinger at 6:00pm has been moved from Ballinger to our Jim Ned Football Stadium due to a water main break in Ballinger still under repair. Due to the circumstances, no ticket needed to enter the gate for this game. No refunds for tickets already purchased.

Enter with a face-covering, then on the honor system for face-covering & social distancing. We do have some COVID cases in the Jim Ned area, so please distance & face-cover as needed to better ensure we do not have to close down our schools & can continue to have games!

Our JNHS leadership, faculty, & staff will honor our seniors today through Cap & Gown Celebration Stations! Roll Tribe!
#weloveourseniors
shared_text:
Jim Ned High School
May 7 at 8:14 PM ·

SENIORS 🎓

Drive Through Cap and Gown Pick Up is TOMORROW! May 8th
This is more than a time to get your cap and gown, this is a time for us to show you just how much we care about you and want to celebrate you.
You will enter the front parking lot of the school using the entrance closest to the Middle School. We will then direct you through our "Celebration Stations" all the way around to the exit in the back. Please go by the First Letter of your Last Name for your time slot.
A -E 9am-10am
F - He 10am- 11am
Hi - M 11am- 12pm
N - R 1pm- 2pm
Sa - St 2pm- 3pm
T - W 3pm-4pm
Can't wait to see all of you! Bring your smile:) You're going to need it:)

post_text:
JNCISD Parents & Staff:

We appreciate everyone’s quick feedback on our surveys. Very helpful in our decision making. JNCISD will be closing for students through next Tuesday (3/24/20). Students will start back to school on Wednesday (3/25/20). We will bring staff back on Monday 3/23 to begin planning for a possible long-term closure. As we have stated all along, these plans are subject to change given the nature of the virus. So stay tuned for future communication. Also, we are working on a feeding program for those that qualify. Stay tuned on that as well. Thanks for your continued prayers & support for our JN community. Tribe Strong!
text:
JNCISD Parents & Staff:

We appreciate everyone’s quick feedback on our surveys. Very helpful in our decision making. JNCISD will be closing for students through next Tuesday (3/24/20). Students will start back to school on Wednesday (3/25/20). We will bring staff back on Monday 3/23 to begin planning for a possible long-term closure. As we have stated all along, these plans are subject to change given the nature of the virus. So stay tuned for future communication. Also, we are working on a feeding program for those that qualify. Stay tuned on that as well. Thanks for your continued prayers & support for our JN community. Tribe Strong!

post_text: There will be no school for students on Monday, March 16th. Our faculty & staff will report to school on Monday to discuss our plans to deal with the possibility of coronavirus in the district. In addition, on Monday, our staff will reach out to our parents by phone to conduct a brief screening regarding the health and any potential exposure of our students to the virus over Spring Break. With no reported cases in Taylor County at this time, is our goal to ensure our students, staff, & families remain as healthy as possible. We are following all direction from the CDC, DSHS, as well as TEA at this time. Our health & safety remain top priorities in JNCISD! Please continue to exercise all preventative measures in the meantime! Roll Tribe!

post_text:
JNCISD Parents:
We want to make sure you are aware that we are working as diligently as possible to get our former districtwide communication system, SchoolWay, replaced. Our new system is called Blackboard Mass Communications and will include a dedicated Jim Ned Indian app that will be functional in both the Apple & Android environments. We apologize for the delay in rolling this out, but we anticipate it being ready in approximately 1-month. In the meantime, continue to follow your children's campus/district news through our various websites, social media, call-outs, etc. Thanks & Go Big Red!

post_text: The Jim Ned CISD Board of Trustees recently recognized JNHS student, Max Rowe, for his outstanding accomplishment in the 2020 Nat'l Merit Scholarship Program. text:
Jim Ned CISD has an Early Release this coming Friday, September 13, 2019 for our annual Homecoming Festivities. Elementary will dismiss at 1:20pm and MS/HS at 1:40pm. What an exciting week as we celebrate Homecoming and welcome our JNHS Alumni back to town! Go Big Red!

Just for fun, here are some yearbook pics from Homecoming 1989 (30 years ago) & 2014 (5 years ago)! Enjoy!

post_text: Congrats to our Jim Ned Lady Indians who were named to our 2019 Homecoming Court today! Pictured left to right are: Lanie Allen (freshman); Claire Graham (sophomore); Faith Morgan (junior); & Senior Homecoming Queen Candidates Taylor Benton, Chancie Barlow, & Laramie Hodges!

post_text: Jim Ned CISD is excited to introduce you to our brand new district Facebook page! It is our goal to increase and improve upon our communication with our JN families, fans, and alumni with this page and our other various media. Spread the word about our JNCISD page and expect to hear about our many successes and other important information throughout the school year! We greatly appreciate the support of our awesome Jim Ned CISD community! Go Big Red!
